Pre-Game Insights: Netherlands are within a point of guaranteeing progress to Euro 2024's knockout stages.
The Oranje should have a full squad available, as back-up striker Brian Brobbey has now recovered from a hamstring injury sustained in training last week.
Ronald Koeman may opt for continuity in the final third, which would see Memphis Depay spearhead a 4-2-3-1 formation.
Cody Gakpo, Xavi Simons, and either Jeremie Frimpong or Donyell Malen will provide support from behind.
Tijjani Reijnders is set to keep his place in midfield, though PSV pair Jerdy Schouten and Joey Veerman could be paired instead if Koeman moves the AC Milan star further forward.
Captain Virgil van Dijk will again join Nathan Ake and Inter Milan teammates Stefan de Vrij and Denzel Dumfries in the Dutch back four.
Brighton & Hove Albion goalkeeper Bart Verbruggen has now established himself as the Netherlands' number one, keeping six clean sheets in his last 10 matches.
